COMPONENT NAME: IKM XML Control Append COMPONENT VERSION: 11.1.2.6 AUTHOR: Oracle COMPATIBILITY: ODI 11.1.2 and above
Description: Writes data into an XML memory table and has an option to commit the data to the file.
Notes: - If the ROOT_TABLE option is set, you have the option of only using a target with no source. This will ensure that only one row is set. - If a path is entered into the XML_PATH field, the current memory data will be written out to a file. - If TRUNCATE_SCHEMA is set to YES, the whole schema will be truncated.
Restrictions: - The FLOW_CONTROL option calls the Knowledge Control Module to isolate the errors. The flow is first stored in the flow table (created dynamically) before performing the control. - When using FLOW_CONTROL or STATIC_CONTROL, be sure that you have set the <root table> option in the XML JDBC properties. - When using the RECYCLE_ERRORS option, you have to set an Update Key for your interface.
Check this option if you want to insert new data in the target table
Use this option to perform a flow control. You should also select an appropriate Knowledge Control Module (KCM) in your interface.
Check this option to control the target table after the insert operation

Truncate the whole XML schema. Set this to yes to clear all data in memory. This should be set to true in the first interface that loads the XML file. When set to YES, be sure to set a value for the ROOT_TABLE option.
Check this option if you want to delete all rows
Create an XML file. This should be set to true in the last interface that loads the XML file. The path of the file to create is passed in in the XML_PATH option.
Set this value to the root table in your XML model. This should be the firt entry in your hierarchy view in the model.

insert into <%if (odiRef.getUserExit("FLOW_CONTROL").equals("1")) {%><%=odiRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","W")%><%} else {%><%=odiRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A")%><%}%> (<%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ", ", "", "INS")%>) select <%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ", ", "", "INS")%> from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> E where not exists (select '?' from <%=odiRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","W")%> <%=odiRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> T where <%=odiRef.getColList("", "\t\tT.[COL_NAME]=E.[COL_NAME]", "\nand", "", "UK")%> ) and E.ORIGIN='<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ORIGIN")%>' and E.ERR_TYPE='<%=odiRef.getInfo("CT_ERR_TYPE")%>'

insert into <%=odiRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%> (<%=odiRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ", ", "", "INS AND !TRG")%>) select <%=odiRef.getPop("DISTINCT_ROWS")%> <%=odiRef.getColList("", "\t[EXPRESSION]", ",\n", "", "INS AND !TRG")%> from <%=odiRef.getFrom()%> where (1=1) <%=odiRef.getJoin()%> <%=odiRef.getFilter()%> <%=odiRef.getJrnFilter()%> <%=odiRef.getGrpBy()%> <%=odiRef.getHaving()%>
